  "text": "Three source files in the Express.js repository reference the deprecated req.host property. First, lib/request.js (lines 451-456) contains the definition of the deprecated req.host property, implemented as a getter that returns this.hostname with a deprecation message 'req.host: Use req.hostname instead'. The file includes a TODO comment indicating the intention to change req.host behavior in a future major version. Second, test/req.host.js contains comprehensive test cases for the deprecated req.host property, testing its behavior in various scenarios including with trust proxy settings, IPv6 hosts, port handling, and when the Host header is null. This test file specifically exercises the req.host property as distinct from the newer req.hostname replacement. Third, History.md contains multiple changelog entries documenting the history and deprecation of req.host: it mentions the addition of req.host in version 3.0.0beta2, fixes in version 4.1.2 for IPv6 literals, the introduction of req.hostname as the correct replacement and explicit deprecation of req.host in version 4.3.0, and a fix for req.host when using trust proxy hops count in version 4.12.1. All three files are essential for understanding the deprecated req.host API, its replacement by req.hostname, and how it was tested and maintained throughout Express versions."
}

